modules.description: Implements basic integer operations including comparison, predecessor, successor, and distance calculation. Works directly with integers wrapped in the `t` type. Useful for precise integer manipulation in contexts like range iteration, sorting, or difference calculation.

This module provides set-theoretic operations (union, intersection, difference), element transformations (mapping, filtering), and ordered traversal capabilities for immutable sets parameterized by an ordered type. It works with sets whose elements are compared and ordered using a provided `compare` function, supporting bulk conversions to/from lists and sequences, subset iteration, and size-aware operations. Specific use cases include managing sorted collections with efficient membership queries, implementing algorithms requiring ordered set intersections, and processing hierarchical data through recursive set partitioning.

This module implements set-theoretic operations, ordered traversal, and element transformations for immutable sets parameterized by an ordered type. It supports efficient membership queries, ordered set intersections, and recursive set partitioning over elements with a defined comparison function. Additionally, it provides precise integer manipulation for tasks like range iteration and difference calculation.
